children.tooltip: Max Tokens helps you control api token response and context window for the specified model. Optional field.
Tokens Per Minute. You can control how many maximum Tokens you want this model to serve.
This is Model Group Name which will be used during call to the LiteLLM Endpoint.
Output token cost. This is an optional field however required if you want to manage Budget and Spending through Proxy.
Request Per Minute. You can control how many maximum requests you want this model to serve.
This is the model name which LiteLLM proxy will call to the LLM Provider.
This is the LLM Provider's Base URL (Ex - OpenAI Base URL).
API Key as created in the AI API Provider. Ex - OpenAI API Key. If running local models. Type "Blank" here.
Input token cost. This is an optional field however required if you want to manage Budget and Spending through Proxy.

children.text: To Change any value, please update the values and press Modify Button
